  "tabnet_exclusion_rationale": "TabNet (Arik & Pfister, 2021) is a deep-learning architecture designed to be competitive with GBMs specifically on LARGE tabular datasets (the paper's own benchmarks use 100K-10M+ row datasets); on ~74K rows spread across 4 classes it has no demonstrated advantage over tuned gradient boosting, its stochastic feature-masking makes per-instance explanations less reproducible than SHAP on a tree model, and it would add a full PyTorch dependency to a FastAPI microservice that is otherwise deliberately lightweight (scikit-learn/XGBoost/LightGBM/CatBoost only). Excluded as a documented, deliberate scope decision, not an oversight."
}